	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />100 IF A&gt;0 GOTO 120 seems more likely.<br /><br />A bigger quirk of old BASIC interpreters though is that they'd outright ignore whitespaces. No, I'm not making this up. You could write the above as 100IFA&gt;0GOTO120 and that stuff would work on such interpreters (on the other hand, &quot;GO TO&quot; instead of &quot;GOTO&quot; would work for the same reason too). The reason for this is that internally they encode everything as tokens, and there isn't any reason to keep whitespace in such stuff. Not sure if Famicom BASIC does this (I know SC-3000 BASIC did).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
