	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Famicom Family Computer (V2)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One test for old basic interpreters is the FORK=ATOM test.  Some treat it as two variables named fork and atom, and others treat it as FOR K = A TO M.<br />Family Basic seems to treat it as FOR K = ATOM which is a syntax error.  So it matches the first keyword it finds after whitespace instead of a variable name beginning with those letters. But a keyword contained inside a variable name is ignored.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


